column5: Went down to the river again for an hour. Managed to catch a new PB. This one hit a 5" storm swim bait. What a fight! She was released to swim again.
wow...that thing has got a belly!  good job on the PB.
Very cool.  How do those guys fight?  I have never caught one.  Are they like a bass? (Jumping etc)?
They don't jump, but they fight much harder than a black bass. They just pull line really hard and take long runs. Its an amazing fight and lots of fun, especially if you catch them on top water.
Matt good to see ya out fishing again.Very nice poisson
WOW!  It's nice to see a report from ya out that way, it's been a while I think. edit: uh i just realized u posted one a couple days ago lol, but before that it's been a while
It been a while since a report. I was busy with finishing my dissertation. A hybrid is a cross between a striped bass and a white bass.
It's a cross between a white bass and a striped bass, also known as a Wiper.
Great job on the PB!  looks like it would be a great fight from shore!
Wow, nice fish Matt!  Looks like some great shore fishing your way.  Love the reports from the south and seeing some 'exotic' species.
WTG Matt     Beauty Keep them reports coming!!! Leechman
